    include($_GET[&#39;page&#39;] . &#39;.php&#39;);  // example only, don&#39;t do this!


Opposed to accessing `https://example.com/test.php` directly where the constant has not been defined:

    // test.php
    defined(&#39;INDEX&#39;) || define(&#39;INDEX&#39;, false);

It is just like other variables that may or may not be set, such as in the example above when accessing `https://example.com/index.php`:

    isset($_GET[&#39;page&#39;]) || $_GET[&#39;page&#39;] = &#39;default&#39;;
